George Carney https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/George_Carney 0 George Carney (21 November 1887 – 9 December 1947) was a British stage and film actor. He worked in the Liverpool Cotton Exchange, in a furniture business, then in the Belfast shipyards. He then took up concert work and entered vaudeville before eventually turning to film.
